<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She recently spoke out in defence of her Britain's Got Talent co-judge Ashley Banjo over his dance troupe Diversity's Black Lives Matter-inspired performance. </p>

<p>But Amanda Holden appeared to put the ongoing controversy aside as she had a Marilyn Monroe moment while twirling into Tuesday donning a white midi dress. </p>

<p>The Heart presenter, 49, flaunted her toned sun-kissed pins as she twisted in the broderie anglaise shirt dress at the Global Radio studios in central London. </p>

